title: PT: Merleau-Ponty

; 1908-1961: Merleau-Ponty

* We are not immaterial centers of consciousness; we cannot perceive or act without our bodies.
* Each one of us has a unique position in space and time which affects how we experience the world.
* The human body is an object and a subject at the same time.